///////Creating a Function/////////////////////////////////
function is defined using the def keyword. 
function has no body bracket({...})

  def functionName():
      statement-1
      statement-2
      .
      .
    

/////Example////////////////////////////////////////////

    def my_function():
      print("Hello from a function")


///////Call a Function///////////////////////////////////

    def my_function():
      print("Hello from a function")

    my_function()

//////Parameter passing/////////////////////////////////

    def my_function(child3, child2, child1):
      print("The youngest child is " + child3)

    my_function("Karim","Rahim", "Jobbar")   //calling function and parameter pass
    my_function(child1 = "Emil", child2 = "Tobias", child3 = "Linus")   //calling function and parameter pass
    
///////Function with initialize parameter///////////////
def hello2(fname, lname="Islam"):
    print(f"Full Name: {fname} {lname}")

hello2("Md. Touhidul")

//////Arbitrary Arguments, *args////////////////////////
If you do not know how many arguments that need to passed into function, then add a * before the parameter name

    def my_function(*kids):
      print("The youngest child is " + kids[2])

    my_function("Karim","Rahim", "Jobbar") 


//////Arbitrary Keyword Arguments, **kwargs//////////////
If you do not know how many keyword arguments that will be passed into your function, add two asterisk: ** before the parameter name

    def my_function(**kid):
      print("His last name is " + kid["lname"])

    my_function(fname = "Tobias", lname = "Refsnes") 


 
